<p>I want to produce a plot with two y-axis and apply multiple datasets to one of the axis. For example</p>  <pre><code>[hAx,hLine1,hLine2] = plotyy([x1',x2',x3'],[y1',y2',y3'],x4,y4); </code></pre>  <p>where <code>x1</code> and <code>y1</code> are <code>1000x1</code>-arrays, <code>x2</code> and <code>y2</code> are <code>2000x1</code>-arrays and <code>x3</code> and <code>y3</code> are <code>3000x1</code>-arrays. The range of the arrays is more or less the same. When i try producing this plot, MATLAB gets me an error saying</p>  <blockquote>   <p>Error using horzcat Dimensions of matrices being concatenated are not   consistent.</p> </blockquote>  <p>Is there any workaround for this error?</p>  <p>EDIT: Here's my real code, which is not working:</p>  <pre><code>[hAx,hLine1,hLine2] = plotyy([erg_cm.Time.data,erg_cm.Time.data,t',t'],...     [erg_cm.Car_FxFL.data,erg_cm.Car_FxFR.data,Fx(1,:),Fx(2,:)],...     erg_cm.Time.data,diff); </code></pre>  <p>And my original data:</p>  <ul> <li><code>erg_cm.Time.data</code> is <code>1x4001</code></li> <li><code>t</code> is <code>80300x1</code></li> <li><code>erg_cm.Car_FxFL.data</code> is <code>1x4001</code></li> <li><code>erg_cm.Car_FxFR.data</code> is <code>1x4001</code></li> <li><code>Fx</code> is <code>4x80300</code></li> <li><code>diff</code> is <code>1x4001</code></li> </ul>